{{Infobox organization | name = Académie des sciences, lettres et arts de Marseille | native_name = | image = | image_size = | alt = | caption = | map = | map_size = | map_alt = | map_caption = | map2 = | map2_size = | map2_alt = | map2_caption = | abbreviation = | motto = ''Primis Renascor Radiis'' | predecessor = | merged = | successor = | formation = <!--e.g. use {{start date|YYYY|MM|DD|df=y}}--> | founder = [[Louis XV]] | extinction = <!--e.g. use {{end date and age|YYYY|MM|DD}}--> | merger = | type = | status = | purpose = | headquarters = | location = [[Marseille]] | coords = <!--{{coord|LAT|LON|display=inline,title}}--> | region = [[Bouches-du-Rhône]] | services = | membership = 40 members elected by their peers | language = [[French language|French]] | sec_gen = | leader_title = | leader_name = | leader_title2 = | leader_name2 = | leader_title3 = | leader_name3 = | leader_title4 = | leader_name4 = | board_of_directors = | key_people = | main_organ = | parent_organization = | subsidiaries = | secessions = | affiliations = [[Conférence nationale des académies des sciences, lettres et arts]] | budget = | staff = | volunteers = | slogan = | website = <!--{{url|example.com}}--> | remarks = | formerly = | footnotes = }} The '''Académie de Marseille''', officially the '''Académie des sciences, lettres et arts de Marseille''', is a French [[learned society]] based in [[Marseille]]. It was founded in 1726 and includes those in the city involved in [[the arts]], [[Literature|letter]]s, and [[science]]s.
==History== The Académie de Marseille was created by [[letters patent]] of [[Louis XV]] in August 1726, which stated in particular that the number of members would be limited to twenty. The founding document furthermore stated that all twenty members must live in [[Marseille]]. However, the actual number of founding members was twenty-one, due to the insistence of {{ill|Jean-Pierre Rigord|fr}} that [[Henri François Xavier de Belsunce de Castelmoron|Henri de Belsunce]] also be offered membership. This was rectified in 1730 when {{ill|Joseph-Félix de Gravier|fr}} resigned from the Académie and was not replaced.
