{{Infobox video game | title = House Flipper | image = House Flipper.jpg | alt = | caption = | developer = Empyrean | publisher = PlayWay S.A.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.playway.com/news-eng-2/652-house-flipper|title=House Flipper on Playway|last=|first=|date=|website=Playway |publisher=|access-date=}}</ref> | series = ''House Flipper'' | engine = [[Unity (game engine)|Unity]] | platforms = [[Windows]], [[macOS]] | release = 17 May 2018 | genre = [[Simulation game|Simulation]] | modes = }}
'''''House Flipper''''' is a simulation game that was developed by Polish indie studio Empyrean and released by PlayWay S.A. through [[Steam (software)|Steam]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.architecturaldigest.com/story/house-flipper-game|title=House Flipper Is a New Computer Game Taking the Internet by Storm|last=|first=|date=|work=Architectural Digest|access-date=2018-06-26|language=en}}</ref> It was released on May 17, 2018. It became a bestseller on Steam.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://thespinoff.co.nz/games/03-06-2018/house-flipper-is-the-renovation-simulator-for-the-eternally-renting-millennial/|title=House Flipper is the renovation simulator for the eternally renting millennial|date=2018-06-03|work=The Spinoff|access-date=2018-06-26|language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.rockpapershotgun.com/2018/05/17/house-flipper-renovation-game-released/|title=Handyman ’em up House Flipper released|date=2018-05-17|website=Rock, Paper, Shotgun|language=en-US|access-date=2018-06-26}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.polygon.com/2018/5/21/17377110/house-flippers-steam-best-seller|title=A home repair simulator is one of Steam’s best-sellers|work=Polygon|access-date=2018-06-26}}</ref>
== Gameplay == Gameplay involves fixing up properties in order to create a profit. Tasks that can be performed include painting, laying down tile, cleaning, installations, and demolition.{{citation needed|date=June 2018}}
== Reception == ''House Flipper'' received "mixed or average reviews" according to [[review aggregator]] [[Metacritic]],<ref>{{cite web |title=House Flipper for PC Reviews |url=http://www.metacritic.com/game/pc/house-flipper |website=Metacritic |publisher=CBS Interactive |accessdate=28 June 2018}}</ref> with multiple reviewers commenting that fixing up the homes is satisfying while questioning its long-term playability. [[Kotaku]] reviewed the game, stating that they found it satisfying to fix up homes that are "often extremely gross or ugly" and that "Manifesting your vision of a decent, sellable house onto these garbage heaps feels amazing—especially because it happens on such a granular scale."<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://kotaku.com/steam-top-seller-house-flipper-makes-it-fun-to-watch-pa-1826205207|title=Steam Top Seller House Flipper Makes It Fun To Watch Paint Dry|last=D'Anastasio|first=Cecilia|work=Kotaku|access-date=2018-06-26|language=en-US}}</ref> Game Informer was more mixed, writing that "Flipping your first few houses is fun, but the game doesn’t have the scope or flexibility to stay interesting for long".<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.gameinformer.com/review/house-flipper/a-definite-fixer-upper|title=House Flipper Review – A Definite Fixer-Upper|work=Game Informer|access-date=2018-06-26|language=en}}</ref> PC Gamer was critical, stating that "There's a definite satisfaction in taking a gross room and making it look nice, and it's pretty cool that you can knock down (and rebuild) walls, but I just don't find the act of slowly and mechanically painting and cleaning much fun, especially with the knowledge that my actual house could do with a bit of that."<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.pcgamer.com/house-flipper-is-like-viscera-cleanup-detail-only-for-super-gross-houses/|title=House Flipper is like Viscera Cleanup Detail only for super gross houses|last=|first=|date=|work=PC Gamer|access-date=2018-06-26|language=en}}</ref>
