'''Skippy Blair''' (born 1924<ref name="SD"/>{{rp|147}}) is a ballroom dancer who is credited with popularizing "[[West Coast Swing]]."<ref>{{cite book|last=Kassing|first=Gayle|url=https://books.google.co.jp/books?id=_lLoTsT2X5EC&pg=PA262&lpg=PA262#v=onepage&q&f=false|title=History of Dance: An Interactive Arts Approach|year=2007|page=262|publisher=Human Kinetics|isbn=978-0-73606-035-6|via=Google Books|accessdate=May 11, 2016}}</ref> Blair was a member of a group that successfully lobbied the State Legislature in 1988 to have West Coast Swing designated as the official [[List of U.S. state dances|State Dance of California]].{{cn|date=May 2016}} She is also the founder of the Golden State Dance Teachers Association<ref name="SD">{{cite book|last1=Stevens|first1=Tamara|last2=Stevens|first2=Erin|url=https://books.google.co.jp/books?id=Sk1PMHxRHAgC&printsec=frontcover#v=onepage&q&f=false|title=Swing Dancing|year=2011|publisher=[[Greenwood Publishing Group]]|isbn=978-0-313-37517-0|via=[[Google Books]]|accessdate=May 11, 2016}}</ref>{{rp|147}} and a co-founder of the [[World Swing Dance Council]].<ref>{{cite web|last=Bekkache|first=Carine|url=http://archives.varmatin.com/frejus/dossier-quelle-danse-vous-sied-au-pied-dans-lagglomeration-raphaeloise.2100684.html|title=DOSSIER. Quelle danse vous sied au pied dans l'agglomération raphaëloise?|date=April 3, 2015|language=French|trans-title=FOLDER. What suits you dance in front in raphaëloise agglomeration?|website=Var-Matin}}</ref><ref name=hof>[http://www.worldsdc.com/hall-of-fame/skippy-blair/ "Skippy Blair"], National Swing Dance Hall of Fame webpage</ref><ref name="SD" />{{rp|189}}

Blair danced in the 1975 film ''[[Queen of the Stardust Ballroom]]''.<ref name=hof/><ref name="SD" />{{rp|143}}

In 1994, she was inducted into the [[National Swing Dance Hall of Fame]].<ref name=hof/> Her students include US Open champions Jordan Frisbee and [[Tatiana Mollmann]].<ref>https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=LGQzWKlY-ZQ Tribute to Skippy Blair with statements by both dancers attesting to Skippy as their teacher retrieved 9.2016 </ref>

Blair created the Universal Unit System, a complete system of dance notation that allows dancers to "read" a dance much like musicians read music.<ref name=hof/>

